3) Also return a single scalar: overall_earliest_anomaly_ts (the minimum earliest_high_ts across all components), and a compact list of components that have earliest_high_ts equal to that overall earliest time.
Keep outputs bounded (component rows <=20). Store intermediate merged tables in kernel variables but only print the compact per-component table and the overall earliest timestamp and matching components.
